  "text": "PIST [CITATION_1] focuses on indexing individual points rather than 3D meshes. PIST is similar in spirit to 3DBG in that it attempts to optimally partition a collection of points into a variable-sized grid according to the density of the data and query size using a quad-tree like data structure. Unlike 3DBG, PIST is off-line (i.e. it does not adapt to new data being added dynamically).",
